By Ukpono Ukpong, Abuja Following the current outbreak and spread of the dreaded Coronavirus
otherwise known as COVID-19, the Comptroller General, Nigeria Immigration
Service, Muhammad Babandede, has ordered the temporary suspension of processing
of passport and Migrant e-Registration. According to a statement
signed by the Service Public Relations Officer, Sunday James, the suspension is
effective March 23through April 23, in line with government’s
directives on restrictions on International Flight. The Comptroller General said that the Service will take advantage
of this period to “process all pending passport cases and that the public will
be informed when they are ready for collection. “The Service regrets any inconvenience caused the general public
within this period while assuring Nigerians of our continued service.” He said